My sincere sympathy with the family.It's a very sad story but sometimes parents are the ones to blame.
One of my client, Shaukat Ali baught a life insurance policy from me.When it came to pay premium wifey said "OH!, we will pay when the policy comes in not with the application.Guess what the premium was only $30.00 for a quater million ploicy.
This couple made me run around for a good three months and they were making excuses left and right, not picking up the phone, answering machine was full.I even went in person and they did not open the door,I asked the neighbors they said they have no clue.This really got me worried......I was praying and hoped all is well.
Finally 4 months later I saw this lady, Ansar Jaan at Coney Island Ave and asked her how is everything?
She started cyring and told me that her perfectly healthy husband Shaukat Ali had a serious heart atack two months ago and died.
I felt bad and helped her as possibly I could have.I personally went to SSI Office with her helped her in getting Social security benefits took her to various Govt offices taking time out from my busy work schedule just to help her without any greed.She has some benefits but not enough to support her family.Govt said go to school learn english and get a job.As a professional I did my job and I don't feel any guilt.
Ansar Jaan is very sorry now... but its too late...I don't know what will happen to these kids Shaukat left behind without any savings.
